             confirmed the evidence of the last witness.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730626-48-person582">
                  Robert
                   Berry
               <interp inst="t17730626-48-person582" type="surname" value="Berry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730626-48-person582" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730626-48-person582" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This day week Mr. Green sent for me about nine o'clock, and gave me charge of the prisoners; I found the lead and a knife upon him. We went to the brewhouse, and saw some new tiles where the men had been at work, and removing them, we found the lead had been cut away; we laid it down and it matched.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177306260040"></xptr>Brittle's Defence.</p>
               <p>The lead is quite straight; it might match any place; it is impossible they should be able to swear to it.</p>
               <p>Brittle called five witnesses who gave him a very good character.</p>
